As someone who works professionally in the service industry i know what kind of decorum, excellence and patience it takes to work as a server, host, etc especially in the pandemic. Tonight I was ashamed for the staff, General Managers and Owners of the Taco Mac on Lindbergh. I made an online order(which I have done before... last week actually.) And when I arrived there was a tv show or movie being shot next door at tongue and groove.So I called to have my order brought out to my car. I sat on the phone for about 5 minutes waiting on somebody to pick up the phone. But to no avail no one picked up the phone. So I went inside walked up to the host stand where there was a girl standing there waiting and she's been waiting for quite a long time. And it took about 3 to 4 minutes before a guy who was standing there talking to another employee sitting at a table turned around and said do you need something. And I told him that I had to go order and what my name was and he gave me the bag and said here he go. And then I said oh wait I have a sweet tea with my order could I get my sweet tea. And then walks away and walks up to another employee sitting at a table watching one of the sports games. He said you need to go up there that's your problem not mine. Then he goes the back I guess to get my sweet tea and the other young gentleman comes up and says do you need something and I I told him that I believe that somebody forgot my sweet tea and he just said that the other guy and went to go get it. He hands me a tea with no ice in it and no straw and says here you go. Then I get home and realize that they did not put any ranch dressing with my fried pickles. And there is no utensils or anything in the bag. If I was the general manager or the owner of that place I'd be extremely embarrassed! It is absolutely ridiculous that there was only four people at the bar and one table with actual customers and nobody could answer the phone in 5 minutes and an order is incorrect!

I was hoping maybe my last experience with poor and slow service at a taco Mac was a fluke - but after my dinner service last night, I'm doubtful I'd be able to recommend any Taco Mac to a friend or family member.  We arrived at 7:09 pm on a Friday evening to a 50% full dining room. We were promptly seated after the hostess marked us as a tally mark on a notepad (assuming so wait staff is equally given tables?).  It was then we were greeted by our waitress, who we gave our appetizer order to and requested a couple of waters before we decided on if we wanted beers or not. The waters arrived after a few minutes, and the appetizers not shortly thereafter.  We only saw our waitress at random intervals, as the busser did more tending to our table than the waitress did. At one point she did appear to ask if we needed refills on water - which then took her another eight minutes to return to get the cups, and another two minutes to return with full glasses.  Honestly, with the lack of attention, we could have just eaten our appetizers and walked out the door - never to be seen again...and I doubt they would notice.  It was then my boyfriend realized we had been waiting for our food for an hour and asked to see the manager. Funny enough, as soon as the manager left, our food magically appeared, again with the busser doing more of the actual legwork.  (The wings were blisteringly hot, temperature wise, and the fries were lukewarm - leading me to believe the wings got nuked due to sitting out)  That was pretty much the theme of the evening - our busser doing the work of a waiter, on top of cleaning and turning tables, and our waitress randomly making appearances and then vanishing again.  Upon asking for the check, we then had to wait longer to get the check back to close out, and to receive validation. We praised and thanked our busser, for doing easily twice the work of our waitress. And on top of all that - the management didn't really seem apologetic about the wait - just "oh, yeah, uh, our bad".  I'll go back to getting my wings from places that actually appreciate my business - and staying away from overpriced wings with poor service at taco Mac.

So I have to be honest with this review... I’m not usually the one to make a review ,but this establishment needs to hear this and people need to be warned of this place for the current time being until things gets better.  I honestly wanted something simple with a place that could handle. What is taco Mac known for? Wings, beer, burgers, and good little appetizers right? This place was an all time favorite from younger years. I went here went here on the hopes of finding good wings, a beer or two, and some crunchy chips. The unfortunate part is that I only got chips and water between an hour time span. I put my order in and it came out 45 minutes later. Customer service is very vital for this place and I WAS NOT taken care of. I had to talk to the manager of the place and the helper to ask “where is the food?” and “is this place under-staffed”. Between the order getting wrong (10 wings and fries), the bad wait time (totaling to 1.5 hours for a meal), refills taken 10 per each refill after asking a helper and the manager of the establishment. The waiter did not server or refill drinks. Even when my order was wrong I was not about to wait another hour to get the right order. The helper was refilling drinks and the manage got the food. Either something was going on in the kitchen or the waiter was not paying attention. I have high hopes for this place but honestly will not attending this place better. I’m sure there is a better place in Atlanta that has better wings, better customer service, better ways of dealing with a kitchen staff, and a better way to attend to their guests. Hope for better because until then, I’ll put my business somewhere else. Until next time, if ever again.

I am a fan of the Taco Mac restaurant chain, but THIS one needs a new manager.  I work near this restaurant, and I have tight lunch constraints, so I placed my order online. The website estimated my order should be done at a particular time, and I walked in the door at precisely that time to pick up my order. My pick-up time was after the lunch-time rush, and the restaurant was only at 10-15% capacity. No one was at the hostess station, so I waited approximately 4 minutes before someone asked me if I was there to pick up or dine-in.  The food was not yet up front, so she went to the kitchen to check on it. She came back and said it would be another couple of minutes.  At this point, I had been waiting 7 minutes to pick-up my order. I had a seat and waited another 8 minutes (19 minutes in at this point), then out of frustration, I went up and asked the bartender for the manager. The manager had been standing right near me working on his phone and glancing at the TV occasionally before the bartender pointed him out. When he came over to me, I told him about my pick-up time and my long wait. He asked me to wait a minute and he went back into the kitchen. He returned with my order bagged up and ready, but he didn't apologize for the inconvenience, nor did he show concern with the lack of service I had experienced. He asked me if everything was there (in the bag), and when I confirmed so, he said "Cool!"  But it was not cool!  I now had 5 minutes to eat my food and get back to my desk!!  If you can't service online orders in a timely manner, then perhaps you shouldn't be offering online ordering.  I know this restaurant is capable of functioning well, because I have been there when it has. But today...it was pretty bad.
